author_ssm: Marybeth Kavanagh, Jenny Gotwals, Kelly McAnnaney, Joseph Ditta
unittitle_ssm: Larry Racioppo photograph collection
abstract_ssm: The Larry Racioppo photograph collection spans the period from 1989-2017 and contains approximately 932 color and black and white photographs of New York City taken by Racioppo. The bulk of the collection are images of distressed neighborhoods taken while Racioppo worked as a photographer at the Department of Housing Preservation and Development, and of churches in the five boroughs, some housed in former theaters, synagogues, and storefronts.
